    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.00095.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Kirkwood <choice><abbr>N.J.</abbr><expan>New Jersey</expan></choice></name>
                    <date when="1877-11-13"><choice><abbr>Novemb</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 13 <gap reason="illegible" extent="one or two numbers" quantity="2" unit="chars"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend Walt&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Father has been very sick and wishes to see you very badly,<ptr target="n0590"/> he <choice><sic>toled</sic><corr>told</corr></choice> me to stop and tell you Yesterday but I did not find you in when I was there so I thought that I would write a few lines to you; the first thing that he asked me when I got home was if I had seen you. We thought
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.00096.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
            he was dying Saturday night for a time. I had to go after the doctor about 12 o'clock you must come down as soon as you get this letter, come down on the 4 train from <choice><abbr>Phila</abbr><expan>Philadelphia</expan></choice> tomorrow if you can any how I will have to close for the present.</p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>Ever yours</salute>
                <signed>Harry Stafford</signed>
            </closer>
            
